<h1>Problem 516 - 2016 China TST Test 2, P6 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>The diagonals of a cyclic quadrilateral \(ABCD\) intersect at \(P\), and there exists a circle \(\Gamma\) tangent to the extensions of \(AB,BC,AD,DC\) at \(X,Y,Z,T\) respectively. Circle \(\Omega\) passes through points \(A,B\), and is externally tangent to circle \(\Gamma\) at \(S\). Prove that \(SP\perp ST\).</p>
